<example>
    <statement>
        <p> Sketch the graph of each of the following. Find the domain, range, intercepts, and asymptotes.</p>
        <p>
            a) <m>y = 3^{x} + 1</m>  <m> \qquad \qquad \text{b)}\,y = 3^{x + 1}</m> <m>\qquad \qquad \text{c)}\,y = - 9^{- x} + 3</m>
        </p>
    </statement>
    <solution>
        <p>
            <ol marker="a)">
                <li>
                    <p>To get the graph of <m>y = 3^{x} + 1</m>. We start with the graph of <m>y = 3^{x}</m>, which is the basic exponential growth graph, and shift it up 1 unit.</p>
